-bicycle-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Drive-Unit-Crank_Green-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-251499\">&nbsp;</figcaption></figure><p>While Pivot tapped one of the top MTB electric drive systems for their Shuttle with Shimano STEPS, this time they enlisted Fazua for the task. Why? That’s because the Fazua Evation 2.0 system offers unique advantages for a road or gravel e-bike. Essentially two bikes in one, both the battery and the drivepack can be removed from the bike and it can still be ridden with minimal weight penalty.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights.jpg\" alt=\"Fazua powered Pivot E-Vault e-bike system\" width=\"1339\" height=\"692\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1339px) 100vw, 1339px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights.jpg 1339w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-297x153.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-800x413.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-120x62.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-768x397.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-696x360.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-1068x552.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-813x420.jpg 813w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights.jpg 1339w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-297x153.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-800x413.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-120x62.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-768x397.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-696x360.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-1068x552.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Fazua-drivepack-breakdown-with-weights-813x420.jpg 813w\"></a></p><p>Once removed, you can install an optional downtube cover to prevent the battery/drivepack chamber from getting dirty, and the bike will be about 3kg/6.6lbs lighter. When removed, all that’s left is the bottom bracket part of the system which is said to have little impact on the pedaling efficiency of the bike. Perfect for days where you want to do all of the work yourself.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p>But on days where you need a little boost, you can install the 252Wh battery and 250W drivepack to harness 55 Nm of torque for pedal assist up to 28mph in the U.S. Charging the battery is said to take around 3.5h for a full charge, and you can carry a range extender for longer rides.</p><figure id=\"attachment_251506\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-251506\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Pivot-EVault-Power-Mode-Button_Green-2-E-BIKE-e-gravel-bicycle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content